1
00:01:43,541 --> 00:01:44,708
♪

2
00:01:44,791 --> 00:01:47,041
[MAKI]
I left her desk the way it was.

3
00:01:48,583 --> 00:01:51,666
I thought that would make her
happy whenever she came home.

4
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:55,041
Of course,
after those men came,

5
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:56,666
she just vanished.

6
00:01:57,666 --> 00:02:00,708
I’m holding out hope
that she’ll be back, but...

7
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:03,625
[SUIGIN]
Don’t worry.

8
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:05,750
Everything will be okay.

9
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:09,458
Rei will come home.
Count on it.

10
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:12,833
How do you know that?

11
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:16,333
[SUIGIN]
Because I’ll bring her back.

12
00:02:17,291 --> 00:02:19,833
No matter what I have to do.

13
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:25,083
♪

14
00:02:25,166 --> 00:02:26,458
[sheen sound]

15
00:02:28,708 --> 00:02:30,291
-[mugs clink]
-[ALL] Great work!

16
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:31,583
[gulping]

17
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:33,583
♪

18
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:34,500
Ah!

19
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:35,458
[slurp]

20
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:36,791
Woo hoo!

21
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:38,791
[WILD WOLF]
Nothing beats a tall cold one

22
00:02:38,875 --> 00:02:40,333
after a hard day’s work.

23
00:02:40,416 --> 00:02:42,125
[EEYUU]
That was awesome!

24
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:44,791
We wouldn’t be the Gold Hunters
without you, bro!

25
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,291
[WILD WOLF]
I know, I know.

26
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:48,750
Then again,
those newbs were total morons.

27
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:52,041
[EEYUU] True, but we raked in
a tasty million ‘cause of them.

28
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:53,458
[WILD WOLF]
And that, my friends,

29
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:55,166
is why it’s always best to swipe

30
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,666
-from the dumb and loaded.
-[sign buzzes]

31
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:58,416
-[saloon chatter]
-Uh, yeah,

32
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,416
you probably shouldn’t
go around saying that in public.

33
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,375
Uh, why not, babe?

34
00:03:03,458 --> 00:03:04,708
Forget about it.

35
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:06,666
Hey.

36
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,916
[crying]

37
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,000
[FARIN]
Does that guy seem weird to you?

38
00:03:10,083 --> 00:03:11,250
[continues crying]

39
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,750
-[sigh]
-[OTHERS] Uh?

40
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,291
I’ll go ask him what’s up.

41
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:21,541
[sliding]

42
00:03:21,625 --> 00:03:24,041
I’m sorry you had to wait,
my lord.

43
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:26,541
♪

44
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:27,750
It’s ready then?

45
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,291
[GIRL]
Yes, finally.

46
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,833
Well done, Ritrette.
I am pleased.

47
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:36,000
-[RITRETTE] My lord.
-[energy humming]

48
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:38,833
Precious will never
see this coming.

49
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:41,583
I’m looking forward
to the results.

50
00:03:42,916 --> 00:03:44,458
[grunt]
No!

51
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:46,291
You made it for her?

52
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:47,791
For that stupid woman?

53
00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:50,541
Stand down, Koshiriko!

54
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,416
Now that Yuuki Riku is dead,
she’s useless to you!

55
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,208
She’s just a bimbo
with no power.

56
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:58,458
So, why?!

57
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,083
Tell me...

58
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,875
She still has worth,

59
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,541
even if you don’t
understand it.

60
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,250
Be patient, girl.

61
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:08,875
You will soon see.

62
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,458
But, Temujin...

63
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:13,875
[chuckling]

64
00:04:15,041 --> 00:04:16,916
[ALL]
They were wiped out?

65
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,583
Yeah.

66
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:19,916
That’s what he said, anyway.

67
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,583
Back up a bit.

68
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:23,583
We’re talking about
the Generals, right?

69
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,666
But they were
the backbone of Precious.

70
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,208
Each of them
was filthy rich!

71
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:29,666
You’re saying he
was their leader?

72
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:30,958
He looks poor as dirt.

73
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:32,625
I know,

74
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,375
but apparently...

75
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,750
Some insanely strong
woman showed up,

76
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:39,083
stripped ‘em of all
their rare items and cash,

77
00:04:39,166 --> 00:04:40,500
then left ‘em to rot.

78
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:43,250
Poor guy just drank away
his last gold piece.

79
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:45,166
A chick did that?

80
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,750
One person against all of them?

81
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:48,541
Yeah.

82
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:49,833
[WILD WOLF]
I call bull.

83
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:51,833
Was probably just
in-fighting or something.

84
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:55,125
Besides, their leader should
be someone awesome looking.

85
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:56,541
Like me...

86
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:01,375
-[metal clinking]
-[sheen sound]

87
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:02,708
Another day,

88
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:04,666
another newbie to mug!

89
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:07,208
Now, drop your belongings,

90
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,458
or you’ll see
this sword up close.

91
00:05:10,541 --> 00:05:11,916
[whimpering]

92
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,625
No! Mercy, please!

93
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:15,500
We’ll pay whatever you ask!

94
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:17,125
Just don’t kill us!

95
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,708
[chuckling]

96
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,750
You’re not as dumb as you look.

97
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:23,416
Tell ya what. I feel generous,
so here’s a tip.

98
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,250
-[whimpering]
-In Grave Buster,

99
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,916
money is life.

100
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:31,000
So get all that you can!
Bein’ broke is a death sentence.

101
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:32,708
A bare wallet
means a full coffin,

102
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,791
and your account
will get the axe.

103
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:37,291
Bro’s a bona fide wordsmith!
[laughing]

104
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:38,541
That was so lame.

105
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:40,708
He’s bona fide something,
alright.

106
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:42,916
“Your account will get the axe.”

107
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,416
-Awesome!
-[scream]

108
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,250
[screaming]

109
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:49,583
-[grunt]
-[slicing sound]

110
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:50,750
-[sigh]
-[sparkling sound]

111
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:52,708
We got a winner.

112
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:54,375
[chuckle]
How about that?

113
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:56,583
[rattling, beeping]

114
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,166
[cash register bell]

115
00:05:58,250 --> 00:05:59,750
[ka-ching]

116
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:02,750
[laugh] Bro’s financial power
went over 50,000,000!

117
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,291
[gasping, whimpering]

118
00:06:04,375 --> 00:06:06,500
No, no, no!
[gasp]

119
00:06:06,583 --> 00:06:08,750
-My items!
-[energy humming]

120
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:11,000
[slurping, laugh]

121
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,750
Now, let’s see
how much you have.

122
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,208
[BOTH whimpering]

123
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,500
[gunshot]

124
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:17,458
[explosion]

125
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:20,500
[energy whining]

126
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:21,833
[gasping]

127
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:23,916
[whimpering, yelling]

128
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,125
[MAN]
We’re free!

129
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,458
Alright. Who’s dying?

130
00:06:28,541 --> 00:06:29,500
♪

131
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:32,291
You are. But, before you do,

132
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:35,291
you’re gonna let me get a good
look at that sword of yours.

133
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:36,291
Uh,

134
00:06:36,375 --> 00:06:37,666
that a flirt?

135
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,625
[laughing]

136
00:06:39,708 --> 00:06:41,291
-[air rushing]
-[energy humming]

137
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:43,208
[explosion]

138
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,041
[air rushing]

139
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:47,208
[zapping]

140
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:49,625
[ricocheting]

141
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:53,708
[laugh]

142
00:06:58,166 --> 00:06:59,125
[shudder]

143
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:00,333
[cocks gun]

144
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:02,125
[grunt]

145
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:03,583
[cards shuffling]

146
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:05,041
That’s far enough.

147
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:07,833
[PHOEBE]
He’s a loud-mouthed bozo,

148
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:10,791
but he is our leader,
and we will protect him.

149
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:13,458
Well done, guys.
I’m so proud!

150
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:16,458
[WILD WOLF]
Drop it, honey. Nice and easy.

151
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:17,416
[grunt]

152
00:07:18,583 --> 00:07:19,625
[uncocks gun]

153
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,250
-[thud]
-[energy humming]

154
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,458
[ALL gasp]

155
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:27,041
♪

156
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:29,541
-[energy humming]
-[gasping]

157
00:07:33,791 --> 00:07:34,958
Now,

158
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:36,916
hand over the goods, “honey.”

159
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,208
[gasping, groan]

160
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:41,791
Now, hold on.
Let’s talk about this.

161
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:45,458
Spare me, and I’ll hand over
all of my friend’s Buster Items!

162
00:07:45,541 --> 00:07:47,541
The Electron Sword,
Freeze Lance,

163
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:49,416
and Quartet Mark are rare!

164
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,041
For real?

165
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:52,833
Totally called it.

166
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:54,333
Pathetic.

167
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,875
Did I say “rare?”
I meant they’re super rare!

168
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,916
C’mon, it’s not a bad deal!

169
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,208
Right?

170
00:08:00,291 --> 00:08:02,666
Oh wait, I know!
They have, "that!"

171
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,791
Yeah! You know? That one thing?

172
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:06,833
Really valuable?
They try to keep it a secret

173
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:09,166
from everyone, even me!
You should take it!

174
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,416
-[slice]
-[grunt]

175
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,916
[laugh]

176
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,958
That’s right. Like that.

177
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:16,958
[EEYUU]
Oh, bro.

178
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:18,875
This is weirdly refreshing.

179
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:20,916
He’s seriously trash.

180
00:08:21,875 --> 00:08:24,250
This sword drains
an opponent’s financial power?

181
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:25,708
-Useful.
-Uh...

182
00:08:25,791 --> 00:08:27,000
However,

183
00:08:27,083 --> 00:08:28,916
it looks like there’s a catch.

184
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,125
Regardless of who’s
on the pointy end,

185
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:33,666
it drains whoever
has less money.

186
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:36,416
Sucks to be you then.
I got around 50,000,000.

187
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,958
Now, let’s see how much
cash you’re holdin’.

188
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:39,916
[rattling, beeping]

189
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,000
What the hell?

190
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:44,250
-[groan]
-[rattling, beeping continues]

191
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:45,166
[whimper]

192
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:48,833
♪

193
00:08:50,541 --> 00:08:53,166
[WILD WOLF]
You gotta be kidding me!

194
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:56,250
Only five players in the world
have that much money!

195
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,916
Just look at it.

196
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,416
[beep, fizzle]

197
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:02,166
[gasp]

198
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,500
[whimpering]

199
00:09:04,458 --> 00:09:06,541
You’re a Billion Player?

200
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:09,791
[whimpering]

201
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:12,000
[WOMAN]
I don’t mind giving you a taste.

202
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:15,916
If you think you’re man
enough to handle it.

203
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,416
[ALL gasp]

204
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,875
[whimpering]

205
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:20,000
[chuckle]

206
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:20,916
[fizzle]

207
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,000
-[roaring]
-[screaming]

208
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:26,958
[explosion]

209
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:34,291
[breeze blowing]

210
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:38,291
♪

211
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:42,708
[energy humming]

212
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:45,000
I take it you’re ready, Master?

213
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,208
[sigh]

214
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:47,333
Mmm.

215
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,208
I know where I need to go.

216
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,708
[shimmer, twirl]

217
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:54,125
[humming]

218
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:56,708
[roar]

219
00:09:56,791 --> 00:09:58,583
[sparkling]

220
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:08,916
[breeze blowing]

221
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,083
[PHOEBE]
That was too close for comfort.

222
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:13,333
[FARIN] If we hadn’t
been in this barrier...

223
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:14,666
[EEYUU]
Where’s bro?

224
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,500
-[energy humming]
-[ALL] Uh?

225
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,166
Bro!

226
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:20,625
[EEYUU] Are you dead?
Yell if you’re dead!

227
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,250
-[horse neighing]
-[grunt]

228
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:25,291
[PHOEBE]
It’s her.

229
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:27,833
Hey, psycho bitch!

230
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:30,833
You could at least
give us your name.

231
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:33,333
My name is the Collector.

232
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:34,500
♪

233
00:10:34,583 --> 00:10:37,041
You Tomb Raiders
are an eye sore.

234
00:10:37,125 --> 00:10:40,041
One day, I’ll wipe you
from the face of this world!

235
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:41,583
[horses galloping]

236
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:44,208
[laughing maniacally]

237
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:49,500
The Collector...

238
00:10:49,583 --> 00:10:51,416
-[EEYUU] Bro! Wake up!
-[FARIN sighs]

239
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,791
Come on, man!

240
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:54,791
Stay with me,
you’ll be alright!

241
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:57,791
Money... is...

242
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,833
-gone.
-[energy humming]

243
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:03,583
[EEYUU crying]
Bro, no!

244
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:13,291
[WOMAN] We have the name
of the one who defies us.

245
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,125
She goes by the moniker,
“Collector.”

246
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:19,875
-[galloping]
-[thunder]

247
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:22,875
[WOMEN] Those who stand
against Precious,

248
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:25,666
will pay with their life.

249
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:28,666
[thunder]

250
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,166
♪

251
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:32,000
[galloping]

252
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:33,833
[thunder]

253
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:18,083
[SUIGIN]
The Silver Guardian!

